fields.copy: Hill & Gertner Capital Corporation (Hill & Gertner) is a talent-based merchant bank, which invests its own capital and that of third parties, and forms partnerships with proven entrepreneurs who have extensive expertise in their respective industries. Hill & Gertner is a consummate niche player, specializing in forming long-lasting and lucrative relationships with corporate leaders and entrepreneurs in the merchandising sector. Our entrepreneurial and opportunistic ways and personal relationships are the key to our success. At Hill & Gertner, we embrace change, believing that it is a natural by-product of progress. When we see change, we see opportunity. More than this, we have the knowledge, know-how and financial resources to capitalize on the ever-evolving business environment. Hill & Gertner is a merchant banking firm providing capital and related advisory services to mid-market companies and entrepreneurs. We work with retailers, manufacturers, distributors and service providers whose businesses are being affected by expansion, re-tooling, a business climate in flux, and mergers or acquisitions. Moreover, we are not intimidated by financial distress. Our strength is our ability to act quickly and deploy our expertise and capital to maximum effect.

Hill & Gernter Retail Partners (HGRP) is an investment banking and advisory firm specializing in the merchandising sector, including retail and consumer goods. HGRP are also principals and equity investors in successful retail and consumer product companies. HGRP’s services include branding and rebranding mergers and acquisitions, capital solutions, consolidations, restructuring, real estate solutions, and advisory services.

HGRP’s expertise in branding, merchandising, consolidations, restructuring and banking means that it understands a company’s potential and can maximize that value in any kind of transaction. More than any other company in Canada, HGRP knows what it takes to be a successful retailer. Since 1996, HGRP has been involved in retail consumer product transactions totaling well over $1 billion.

HGRP’s principals have visionary, branding, strategic, merchandising and operational skills that are unmatched in the Canadian market. These skills are complemented by an expertise in financial engineering, all of which enables HGRP to provide creative turnkey solutions.

-

Since its formation in 1986, Quadrangle Architects Limited has established itself as one of Canada’s most dynamic architectural firms. The practice was formed by the merger of Klein Taylor Goldsmith Limited (established in 1978) and Curtner Brown Architects (established in 1981). Wide-ranging in its scope and abilities, Quadrangle has assembled a portfolio of projects that illustrates a diverse client list and expertise in a wide variety of building types from corporate to commercial to residential. In addition to its many large-scale projects, Quadrangle is highly regarded for its corporate and commercial interiors carried out by its in-house interior design group.

-

SB Captial Group provides retail consulting services and purchases retail assets, including inventory, equipment, receivables and real property. An affiliate of Schottenstein Stores Corporation, owner and operator of Valve City Department Stores, DSW Designer Shoe Warehouse, Value City Furniture and American Eagle Outfitters, SB performs specialized services for fellow retailers in the areas of management consulting, inventory valuation/liquidation and retail acquisitions, auctions and dispositions.

SB operates throughout North America, South America and Europe with offices in Columbus, Ohio, New York, Toronto, and Birmingham, England. SB’s clients have included Eaton’s Adventure Electronics, White Rose, BiWay, Holt Renfrew and Montgomery Ward.

www.sbcapitalgroup.com

Cynapsus is a specialty pharmaceutical company developing a convenient and easy to use sublingual (oral) thin film strip

for the acute rescue of “off” motor symptoms of Parkinson’s disease. Over one million people in the U.S. and an estimated 5

million people globally suffer from Parkinson's disease. Parkinson’s disease is a chronic and progressive neurodegenerative

disease that impacts motor activity, and its prevalence is increasing with the aging of the population.

-

If it’s true that where there’s Tokyo smoke there’s fire, perhaps it’s because our newest brand is lighting the fashion world

ablaze.

The Tokyo Smoke line is at once sophisticated, authentic and modern, ideal for the man who wants to look good, but doesn’t

want to appear like he’s trying too hard.

-

The Peacock Parade is the discerning shoppers’ answer to elite e-commerce. Their merchandise curators provide members

with a refined collection of affordable luxury, presented amidst flawless aesthetic. By imposing the highest standards of selection,

they maintain the integrity of their brands. Members experience the elegance of couture, the adrenaline of a sample sale

and the sophistication of service traditionally reserved for the privileged.

www.thepeacockparade.com

-

TFW

Seven Continents is a boutique design resource that manufactures innovative products for visual merchandising and retail store interiors.

Seven Continents’s core competencies are upholstered forms, fabric and furniture, as well as other specialties, both proprietary and custom, which include mannequins, fixtures and accessories. The company specializes in the design, manufacture, delivery and installation of high-quality custom wood and metal fixtures. Seven Continents customers are successful retailers requiring marketing displays for their stores. Customers include many top North American retailers such as Marshall Fields, Macy’s, Neiman Marcus, Saks Fifth Avenue, Disney, Tommy Bahama, Fossil, Abercrombie & Fitch and Holt Renfrew.

www.sevencontinents.com
